snippet.textDisplay:
I found this video thanks to Youtube showing it in the side bar. Being Mexican, at first I was horrified, but once I started to look at how you cooked the chorizo, I went... wait, this might actually work! And seeing the final result, yeah, this was a great idea. I'll probably try this and see how it turns out (honestly the local chorizo brands aren't that good) and surprise my family with it.

If you can find it, you might also want to try mixing Spanish chorizo into this - it's sturdier and closer to Italian sausage, and has its own type of spices that are somewhat different to Mexican / crumbly style chorizo. I would cook both separately, cutting the Spanish one into bits since it takes a bit longer to cook, then when you mix the beef stock and the sauce, combine them.

Thanks for the video!
